                <h1>Understanding Background Research: A Guide</h1>
                <p>Background research involves gathering existing information about a topic before embarking on a project, study, or investigation. It helps to understand the current landscape, identify gaps in knowledge, and inform the methodology. By reviewing literature, studies, and previous findings, researchers can build a strong foundation for their work.</p>
